 This study will include children who will be randomly allocated to either receive the malaria vaccine adjuvanted with Aluminium Hydroxide or the Verorab control.

 Each participant will receive 3 immunizations, without the clinical investigators or the participants themselves knowing what has been given.

 They will then be followed-up for immediate reactions to vaccination, extended safety profile and immunological response associated with protection from malaria.

 These children will be followed up for over a longer term of two years.

 Blood will be taken to evaluate the biological safety parameters and also the immune responses.

